[[File:Von mueller.jpg|thumb|Ferdinand von Mueller]]
'''''Fragmenta phytographiae Australiae''''' is a series of papers written by the [[Government of Victoria (Australia)|Victorian Government]] botanist [[Ferdinand von Mueller]] in which he published many of his approximately 2000 descriptions of new taxa of [[Flora of Australia|Australian plants]].<ref name=ASBS/> The papers were issued in 94 parts between 1858 and 1882 and published in 11 volumes.<ref name=BHL>{{cite web|title=Fragmenta phytographiæ Australiæ /contulit Ferdinandus Mueller.|publisher=Biodiversity Heritage Library|url=https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/bibliography/287|accessdate=29 April 2011}}</ref><ref name="Regardfully Yours">{{cite book|author1=von Mueller, Ferdinand |author2=Home, Roderick Weir |title=Regardfully Yours: Selected Correspondence of Ferdinand von Mueller|volume=3|page=23|publisher=International Academic Publishers|location=Bern, Switzerland|year=2006|isbn=3-906757-10-2}}</ref> Though a 12th volume was apparently planned, it was not published.<ref name="Regardfully Yours"/> It is the only scientific journal in Australia that has been completely written in Latin.<ref name=ASBS>{{cite web|title=Publications: History of Systematic Botany in Australasia|publisher=Australian Systematic Botany Society Inc.|url=http://www.anbg.gov.au/asbs/publications/history_sys_bot_aust.html|accessdate=29 April 2011}}</ref>

One of the illustrators of the series was [[Ludwig Becker (explorer)|Ludwig Becker.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.anbg.gov.au/biography/becker-ludwig.html|title=Becker, Ludwig - biography|last=Hewson|first=Helen|date=27 November 2015|website=www.anbg.gov.au|publisher=Australian National Herbarium|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-08-06}}</ref> 

