{{Orphan|date=October 2011}}
The following details are for the programmes that [[ITV Breakfast]] have broadcast.
ITV Breakfast is the breakfast television franchise for the UK's [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] network. It began broadcasting on 6 September 2010 as replacement for [[GMTV|GMTV Limited]].
==''Good Morning Britain''== '''''[[Good Morning Britain (2014 TV programme)|Good Morning Britain]]''''' is the weekday [[breakfast television]] programme on the British commercial [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] network that broadcasts on weekday mornings from 06:00 to 08:30 and is presented by [[Susanna Reid]], [[Piers Morgan]], [[Ben Shephard]] and [[Kate Garraway]]. It features news and entertainment stories interspersed with celebrity interviews, competitions, consumer and health items and news reports from the regions.
==''Lorraine''== '''''[[Lorraine (TV programme)|Lorraine]]''''' is the early weekday morning, lifestyle and entertainment show for the British [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] network, presented by [[Lorraine Kelly]]. [[ITV Breakfast]] produces ''Lorraine'', which airs every weekday from 08:30 until 09:25, following ''[[Good Morning Britain (2014 TV programme)|Good Morning Britain]]''. The programme replaced Kelly's previous show, ''[[List of GMTV programmes#GMTV with Lorraine|GMTV with Lorraine]]''.<ref name=PressPack>[http://www.itv.com/documents/doc/Lorraine%20Press%20Pack.doc Lorraine Presspack] ITV.com, 31 August 2010</ref>
==[[CITV]] and ''Mini CITV''== [[CITV]] is broadcast each weekend on ITV Breakfast on weekends originally from 06:00-09:25 however since May 2011 has been cut short by the remaining hour.
==''Dinner Date''== '''''[[Dinner Date]]''''' is a [[dating]] [[cooking]] [[game show]] created by [[Hat Trick Productions]]. The first series started on 9 August 2010 and ended on 26 November of the same year and the second series started on 20 June 2011 and ended on 29 July of the same year, both series aired on Monday to Friday afternoon at 5:00pm. The third series started on 15 April 2012 with episodes 1-16, 22, 28 and 34-35 airing on Sunday mornings at 8:25am on [[ITV Breakfast]] whilst episodes 17-21, 23-27 and 29-33 aired its usual Monday to Friday afternoon at 5:00pm and episodes 36-38 aired around the Christmas holidays from 26 to 28 December 2012, which was the date the third series ended its run.
